The paper deals with optimization methods for SVMs, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV). The focus is on mini-batch methods, which are a popular approach for speeding up stochastic optimization algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the spectral norm of the data, which is a common concept in numerical analysis and optimization (cs.NA).
